_source.title: Cloudflare - Snapshot
_source.description: Get a quick overview of the most important metrics from your websites and applications on the Cloudflare network.

_source.title: Cloudflare - Performance (Requests, Bandwidth, Cache)
_source.description: Identify and address performance issues and caching misconfigurations. Metrics include total vs. cached bandwidth, saved bandwidth, total requests, cache ratio, top uncached requests, and more.

_source.title: Cloudflare - Reliability
_source.description: Get insights on the availability of your websites and applications. Metrics include origin response error ratio, origin response status over time, percentage of 3xx/4xx/5xx errors over time, and more.

_source.title: Cloudflare - Performance (Static vs. Dynamic Content)
_source.description: Get insights into the performance of your static and dynamic content, including slowest URLs.

_source.title: Cloudflare - Security (Overview)
_source.description: Get insights on threats to your websites and applications, including number of threats stopped, threats over time, top threat countries, and more.

_source.title: Cloudflare - Performance (Hostname, Content Type, Request Methods, Connection Type)
_source.description: Get insights into your most popular hostnames, most requested content types, breakdown of request methods, and connection type.

_source.title: Cloudflare - Security (Rate Limiting)
_source.description: Get insights on rate limiting protection against denial-of-service attacks, brute-force login attempts, and other types of abusive behavior targeted at your websites or applications.

_source.title: Cloudflare - Security (Bot Management)
_source.description: Cloudflare - Security (Bot Management) Dashboard reliably detects and mitigates bad bots to prevent credential stuffing, spam registration, content scraping, click fraud, inventory hoarding, and other malicious activities.

_source.title: Cloudflare - Security (WAF)
_source.description: Get insights on threat identification and mitigation by our Web Application Firewall, including events like SQL injections, XSS, and more. Use this data to fine tune the firewall to target obvious threats and prevent false positives.
